e filling factors are typically below 30\\%. We also\nfind that the flux of the two polarities is not balanced. From the other half\nof the observed quiet-Sun area $\\sim$50\\% are two-lobed Stokes $V$ profiles,\nmeaning that 23\\% of the field of view can be adequately explained with a\nsingle constant magnetic field embedded in a non-magnetic atmosphere. The\nmagnetic field vector and filling factor are reliable inferred in only 50\\%\nbased on the regular profiles. Therefore, 12\\% of the field of view harbour hG\nfields with filling factors typically below 30\\%. At our present spatial\nresolution, 70\\% of the pixels apparently are non-magnetised.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 26 Apr 2018 14:34:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-04-27"}
